Vice President Biden met with trade association leaders to discuss workforce development and job-driven training. He emphasized the importance of collaboration to provide workers with the skills needed for in-demand jobs. The Vice President called on industry associations to expand successful training programs and encouraged them to work with community colleges. They also discussed initiatives like the Ready to Work Partnership grant competition and Community College Training grants. President Obama assigned the Vice President to lead a reform of training programs to ensure they align with employers' needs and provide good job opportunities. The Vice President is working with various organizations and federal agencies to make the workforce and training system more effective.